article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- — Rahsool Diggins' 25 points helped UMass defeat George Washington 81-67 on Saturday. Diggins added five assists for the Minutemen (12-6, 3-3 Atlantic 10 Conference). Jaylen Curry scored 17 points, shooting 8 for 12, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc. Josh Cohen was 6 of 11 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 15 points, while adding 12 rebounds. Garrett Johnson led the Revolutionaries (14-4, 3-2) in scoring, finishing with 16 points. Darren Buchanan Jr. added 15 points and eight rebounds for George Washington. In addition, Maximus Edwards finished with 13 points, 11 rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
